### Convert Markdown to Lexical Richtext Editor State (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/rich-text/converting-markdown.mdx

This code snippet illustrates how to convert a Markdown string into a Payload CMS Lexical `SerializedEditorState` object, which can then be used in the rich text editor. It leverages the `convertMarkdownToLexical` function from `@payloadcms/richtext-lexical` and requires an `editorConfig` derived from your Payload Config.

```ts
import {
  convertMarkdownToLexical,
  editorConfigFactory,
} from '@payloadcms/richtext-lexical'

const lexicalJSON = convertMarkdownToLexical({
  editorConfig: await editorConfigFactory.default({
    config, // <= make sure you have access to your Payload Config
  }),
  markdown: '# Hello world\n\nThis is a **test**.',
})
```

