### Convert Raw HTML to Lexical Rich Text Editor State in PayloadCMS

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/rich-text/converting-html.mdx

This TypeScript example demonstrates how to convert a raw HTML string into a Lexical rich text editor state using `convertHTMLToLexical`. It requires providing the PayloadCMS configuration and the `JSDOM` library for HTML parsing. This function is useful for importing existing HTML content into the Lexical editor format.

```ts
import {
  convertHTMLToLexical,
  editorConfigFactory,
} from '@payloadcms/richtext-lexical'
// Make sure you have jsdom and @types/jsdom installed
import { JSDOM } from 'jsdom'

const html = convertHTMLToLexical({
  editorConfig: await editorConfigFactory.default({
    config, // Your Payload Config
  }),
  html: '<p>text</p>',
  JSDOM, // Pass in the JSDOM import; it's not bundled to keep package size small
})
```

